FBIS4-38839 "drsov107_a_94020" FBIS-SOV-94-107 Daily Report 2 Jun 1994 RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS Bosnian Serb Leader Karadzic To Visit Moscow 8-12 Jun Bosnian Serb Leader Karadzic To Visit Moscow 8-12 Jun LD0206213994 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1548 GMT 2 Jun 94 LD0206213994 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service Russian BFN [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Konstantin Pribytkov] [Text] Geneva, 2 June -- Bosnian Serb leader Radovan Karadzic plans to visit Moscow next week. The Serbian leader, who is also well known as a poet, said today in an exclusive interview with an ITAR-TASS correspondent in Geneva that the trip is connected with his being awarded the literary Mikhail Sholokhov Prize by the Russian Union of Writers. In addition, Radovan Karadzic intends to make use of his stay in Moscow to have talks about the rapid achievement of peace in Bosnia and Herzegovina. According to the Serbian leader, the trip is planned for about 8-12 June.
